						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall, rock-cut shrine, Mēlaikkōyil temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 7: 978 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of 7 <hi rend="italic">tuḷaippoṉ</hi> by a lady Varaguṇaṉāṭṭi perumāḷ ••• •••, the wife of Sembiyan Irukkuvēḷ and the daughter of Muttaraiyar for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Tirumūlaṭṭāṉattup-perumāṉaḍigaḷ at Tirunalakkuṉṟam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> of Kuṉṟiyūr-nāḍu. She also donated a lamp-stand.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 155.</p>						

						</summary>
